16/12/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The voluntary disarmament campaign formally ended on Monday (15 December), with an estimated 3 per cent of illegal weapons turned in. Now that the campaign is over, amnesty is off the table; those who are caught with illegal weapons face severe sanctions.
In other news Monday, the government approved the construction of a new US embassy building in Skopje, in the vicinity of Kale.
Also Monday, Bulgarian Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov arrived for two-day visit to Skopje to discuss military co-operation possibilities and support for Macedonia's efforts to join NATO.
Meanwhile, Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski met with EU security chief Javier Solana, who arrived for the start of the EU police mission Proxima. (Utrinski Vesnik - 16/12/03; MIA, A1 TV, Makfax - 15/12/03)
